rComments: Lectures is enjoyable. Makes jokes and examples often. Tests are very similar to past exams in which he posts the answers to. Exams are really not hard if u actually tried to understand the concept. And he keeps the avg to around 78-80 so. Dats pretty high. Managed to get 94% on the finals despite getting around 70 on midterm.

Wonderful lecturer. He explained concepts very clearly. I really love how he cares about his students by constantly asking us if we understand what he has been teaching. Game theory is so much more interesting with him teaching it.

His teaching style is dynamic and keeps you awake. He is clear and rigorous which is very important for microeconomics. The only problem of this course are the problem sets :They are so long that you have to give up studying for other courses.   (and they are graded so you have to do them).
